# SMEVCS - Smart Management of EV Charging Station

A Java web application for managing Electric Vehicle Charging Stations built during undergrad.

## Tech Stack
- Java Servlets & JSP
- MySQL Database
- Apache Tomcat 9
- Maven

## Features
- User Registration & Login
- Admin Login & Dashboard
- Manage Charging Slots (Add/Delete)
- Search Slots by City
- Book a Slot & Make Payment
- View Booking & Payment History
- Chatbot Support

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Prerequisites
- Java 11
- Maven
- MySQL
- Apache Tomcat 9

### 2. Database Setup
```sql
mysql -u root
source database/schema.sql
```

### 3. Configure Database
Edit `src/main/java/com/connection/DBConnection.java`:
```java
public static String DBUSER = "root";
public static String DBPASSWORD = "your_password";
```

### 4. Build the Project
```bash
mvn clean package
```

### 5. Deploy
Copy the generated `target/SMEVCS.war` to Tomcat's `webapps/` folder and start Tomcat.

